  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN121.1-kilavi">tōḻiyāṟ ṟalaimaka<supplied>ḷai</supplied> <app><lem>yuṭaṉvarumeṉak</lem><rdg wit="#C5">koṇṭucelkaveṉak</rdg><rdg wit="#NL #C1 #C9">yuṭaṉakameṉṟākak</rdg></app> kēṭṭa <app><lem>talaimakaṉ</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C5 #C7">talaimaṟaṉ</rdg></app> neñciṟkuc collic celavaḻuṅkiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How HE, who had heard that it was said by the confidante to HER that 
            she would come along, prevented going by speaking to his heart.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN121.1">
        <l>nānakai yuṭaiya neñcē <supplied>ka</supplied>ṭunteṟal</l>
        <l>vēṉi ṉīṭiya vāṉuyar vaḻināḷ</l>
        <l>vaṟumai kūṟiya maṇṇīrc ciṟukuḷat</l>
        <l>toṭukuḻi maru<supplied>ṅ</supplied>kiṟ ṟuvvāk kalaṅkal</l>
        <l>kaṉṟuṭai maṭappiṭi kayantalai maṇṇic</l>
        <l>cēṟukoṇ ṭāṭiya vēṟupaṭu vayakkaḷiṟu</l>
        <l>ceṅkōl vāliṇar tayaṅkat tīṇṭic</l>
        <l>coṟipuṟa muriñciya ne<supplied>ṟi</supplied>yayaṉ marāat</l>
        <l>talkuṟu variniḻa lacaiiya nammoṭu</l>
        <l>tāṉvaru meṉpa taṭameṉ ṟōḷi</l>
        <l>yuṟukaṇ maḻava ruruḷ<supplied>kī</supplied>ṇ ṭiṭṭa</l>
        <l>vāṟuceṉ mākkaḷ cōṟupoti veṇkuṭaik</l>
        <l>kaṉmicaik kaṭuva<supplied>ḷi</supplied> yeṭuttaliṟ ṟuṇaicettu</l>
        <l>ve<supplied>ru</supplied>ḷēṟu payiru mā<supplied>ṅ</supplied>kaṭ</l>
        <l>karumuka mucuviṉ kāṉat tāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>We are smiling, heart: on the last day</l>
        <l corresp="1-2">high in the sky when the fierce, scorching summer [heat] has lasted long,</l>
        <l>she with broad soft shoulders, they say, will come in person</l>
        <l>with us in order to rest in the dwindling dappled shade</l>
        <l>of the Kadamba tree near the path on which the transformed strong elephant bull</l>
        <l>rubs [its] itching back, bumping the red-stemmed white clusters</l>
        <l>so that they swayed, [the bull] who had bathed, taking mud,</l>
        <l>washing the soft head of [its] youthful cow that has a calf</l>
        <l>with the muddy water that is not drunk from a pit he dug</l>
        <l corresp="3-9">in the pond short of water, with earth [showing] that speaks of scarcity</l>
        <l>– in the forest of the black-faced langur,</l>
        <l>that place where the startled bull calls,</l>
        <l>thinking of [its] mate because the fierce wind lifts, on the stones,</l>
        <l>the white baskets with the stores of rice of the people going on the road</l>
        <l corresp="11-15">which is cleaved by the [chariot] wheels of suffering warriors.</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
